{
  "texts": [
    "Out of 683 papers, we obtained only 13 primary articles that were relevant to our research topic.",
    "Many articles, albeit interesting, did not present the AI practitioners' views on ethics in AI.",
    "So, we decided to find more relevant articles through snowballing of articles.",
    "\"Snowballing refers to using the reference list of a paper or the citations to the paper to identify additional papers\" (Wohlin 2014).",
    "Snowballing of those 13 articles via forward citations and backward citations was done to find more relevant articles and enrich the overview review quality."
  ]
}